<!-- PAGE 6: ABSTRACT -->
<div class="page">
  <div class="chapter-header">ABSTRACT</div>
  <br>
  <p>Mental health is one of the most critical yet underaddressed challenges facing college students today. Academic pressure, social isolation, relationship difficulties, and financial stress are among the leading contributors to anxiety, depression, and burnout among the student population. Despite the growing awareness of mental health issues, many students lack access to timely, affordable, and stigma-free mental health support.</p>
  <br>
  <p><strong>MindCare</strong> is a web-based student mental health support platform developed to bridge this gap. Built on the Internet Computer Protocol (ICP) using Motoko for backend logic and React/TypeScript for the frontend, MindCare offers a secure, decentralized, and always-available mental health support system tailored specifically for college students.</p>
  <br>
  <p>The platform features a counselor assignment system where students can choose or be assigned to professional counselors, a real-time on-chain chat system for direct student-counselor communication, an AI-powered chatbot for immediate mental health support, automated health checkup reminders, and a comprehensive admin panel for counselor management.</p>
  <br>
  <p>The AI chatbot is rule-based, requiring no external API keys, and recognizes over 18 mental health topics including anxiety, depression, stress, loneliness, academic pressure, and crisis situations. It always directs users to the 988 crisis helpline when serious distress signals are detected.</p>
  <br>
  <p>By leveraging blockchain technology through ICP, MindCare ensures data privacy, security, and permanence while providing students with a familiar, modern interface that encourages engagement and reduces the stigma associated with seeking mental health support.</p>
  <br>
  <p><strong>Keywords:</strong> Mental Health, Student Wellness, ICP, Motoko, React, AI Chatbot, Counselor Management, Web Application, Decentralized Application.</p>
</div>

