<div class="page">
  <h3>APPENDIX C: GLOSSARY</h3>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Term</th><th>Definition</th></tr>
    <tr><td>ICP</td><td>Internet Computer Protocol - A blockchain-based distributed computing platform developed by DFINITY Foundation</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Motoko</td><td>A purpose-built programming language for writing smart contracts on the Internet Computer Protocol</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Canister</td><td>A smart contract unit on ICP that bundles code and data, capable of serving web content directly</td></tr>
    <tr><td>React</td><td>An open-source JavaScript library for building user interfaces, developed by Meta (Facebook)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>TypeScript</td><td>A statically-typed superset of JavaScript that compiles to plain JavaScript</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Tailwind CSS</td><td>A utility-first CSS framework for rapidly building custom user interfaces</td></tr>
    <tr><td>DFD</td><td>Data Flow Diagram - A graphical representation of data flow through an information system</td></tr>
    <tr><td>ER Diagram</td><td>Entity-Relationship Diagram - A visual representation of the data model and relationships</td></tr>
    <tr><td>API</td><td>Application Programming Interface - A set of protocols for building and integrating application software</td></tr>
    <tr><td>CRUD</td><td>Create, Read, Update, Delete - The four basic operations of persistent storage</td></tr>
    <tr><td>UI/UX</td><td>User Interface / User Experience - Design disciplines focused on user interaction and satisfaction</td></tr>
    <tr><td>988 Lifeline</td><td>988 Suicide and Crisis Lifeline - A US national network providing 24/7 crisis support</td></tr>
    <tr><td>On-chain</td><td>Data or processes stored directly on the blockchain, ensuring immutability and decentralization</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Stable Memory</td><td>Persistent storage in ICP canisters that survives canister upgrades</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Rule-based AI</td><td>An AI system that uses predefined rules and pattern matching rather than machine learning models</td></tr>
    <tr><td>UAT</td><td>User Acceptance Testing - Testing conducted by end users to verify the system meets requirements</td></tr>
    <tr><td>HOD</td><td>Head of Department - The senior academic administrator of a university department</td></tr>
    <tr><td>B.Tech</td><td>Bachelor of Technology - An undergraduate engineering degree program</td></tr>
  </table>
